   1 #!/usr/bin/env python
   2 # Note, this script is based off of https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
   3 #
   4 # Hi There!
   5 # You may be wondering what this giant blob of binary data here is, you might
   6 # even be worried that we're up to something nefarious (good for you for being
   7 # paranoid!). This is a base85 encoding of a zip file, this zip file contains
   8 # an entire copy of pip.
   9 #
  10 # Pip is a thing that installs packages, pip itself is a package that someone
  11 # might want to install, especially if they're looking to run this get-pip.py
  12 # script. Pip has a lot of code to deal with the security of installing
  13 # packages, various edge cases on various platforms, and other such sort of
  14 # "tribal knowledge" that has been encoded in its code base. Because of this
  15 # we basically include an entire copy of pip inside this blob. We do this
  16 # because the alternatives are attempt to implement a "minipip" that probably
  17 # doesn't do things correctly and has weird edge cases, or compress pip itself
  18 # down into a single file.
  19 #
  20 # If you're wondering how this is created, it is using an invoke task located
  21 # in tasks/generate.py called "installer". It can be invoked by using
  22 # ``invoke generate.installer``.
  23 # Note, this get-pip.py installer is modified to meet pipenv's needs.
  24 import os.path
  25 import pkgutil
  26 import shutil
  27 import sys
  28 import struct
  29 import tempfile
  30 
  31 # Useful for very coarse version differentiation.
  32 PY2 = sys.version_info[0] == 2
  33 PY3 = sys.version_info[0] == 3
  34 if PY3:
  35     iterbytes = iter
  36 else:
  37 
  38     def iterbytes(buf):
  39         return (ord(byte) for byte in buf)
  40 
  41 
  42 try:
  43     from base64 import b85decode
  44 except ImportError:
  45     _b85alphabet = (
  46         b"0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
  47         b"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz!#$%&()*+-;<=>?@^_`{|}~"
  48     )
  49 
  50     def b85decode(b):
  51         _b85dec = [None] * 256
  52         for i, c in enumerate(iterbytes(_b85alphabet)):
  53             _b85dec[c] = i
  54         padding = (- len(b)) % 5
  55         b = b + b'~' * padding
  56         out = []
  57         packI = struct.Struct('!I').pack
  58         for i in range(0, len(b), 5):
  59             chunk = b[i: i + 5]
  60             acc = 0
  61             try:
  62                 for c in iterbytes(chunk):
  63                     acc = acc * 85 + _b85dec[c]
  64             except TypeError:
  65                 for j, c in enumerate(iterbytes(chunk)):
  66                     if _b85dec[c] is None:
  67                         raise ValueError(
  68                             'bad base85 character at position %d' % (i + j)
  69                         )
  70 
  71                 raise
  72 
  73             try:
  74                 out.append(packI(acc))
  75             except struct.error:
  76                 raise ValueError(
  77                     'base85 overflow in hunk starting at byte %d' % i
  78                 )
  79 
  80         result = b''.join(out)
  81         if padding:
  82             result = result[:-padding]
  83         return result
  84 
  85 
  86 def bootstrap(tmpdir=None):
  87     # Import pip so we can use it to install pip and maybe setuptools too
  88     import pip
  89     from pip.commands.install import InstallCommand
  90     from pip.req import InstallRequirement
  91 
  92 
  93     # Wrapper to provide default certificate with the lowest priority
  94     class CertInstallCommand(InstallCommand):
  95 
  96         def parse_args(self, args):
  97             # If cert isn't specified in config or environment, we provide our
  98             # own certificate through defaults.
  99             # This allows user to specify custom cert anywhere one likes:
 100             # config, environment variable or argv.
 101             if not self.parser.get_default_values().cert:
 102                 self.parser.defaults["cert"] = cert_path  # calculated below
 103             return super(CertInstallCommand, self).parse_args(args)
 104 
 105     pip.commands_dict["install"] = CertInstallCommand
 106     implicit_pip = True
 107     implicit_setuptools = True
 108     implicit_wheel = True
 109     # Check if the user has requested us not to install setuptools
 110     if "--no-setuptools" in sys.argv or os.environ.get("PIP_NO_SETUPTOOLS"):
 111         args = [x for x in sys.argv[1:] if x != "--no-setuptools"]
 112         implicit_setuptools = False
 113     else:
 114         args = sys.argv[1:]
 115     # Check if the user has requested us not to install wheel
 116     if "--no-wheel" in args or os.environ.get("PIP_NO_WHEEL"):
 117         args = [x for x in args if x != "--no-wheel"]
 118         implicit_wheel = False
 119     # We only want to implicitly install setuptools and wheel if they don't
 120     # already exist on the target platform.
 121     if implicit_setuptools:
 122         try:
 123             import setuptools  # noqa
 124 
 125             implicit_setuptools = False
 126         except ImportError:
 127             pass
 128     if implicit_wheel:
 129         try:
 130             import wheel  # noqa
 131 
 132             implicit_wheel = False
 133         except ImportError:
 134             pass
 135     # We want to support people passing things like 'pip<8' to get-pip.py which
 136     # will let them install a specific version. However because of the dreaded
 137     # DoubleRequirement error if any of the args look like they might be a
 138     # specific for one of our packages, then we'll turn off the implicit
 139     # install of them.
 140     for arg in args:
 141         try:
 142             req = InstallRequirement.from_line(arg)
 143         except:
 144             continue
 145 
 146         if implicit_pip and req.name == "pip":
 147             implicit_pip = False
 148         elif implicit_setuptools and req.name == "setuptools":
 149             implicit_setuptools = False
 150         elif implicit_wheel and req.name == "wheel":
 151             implicit_wheel = False
 152     # Add any implicit installations to the end of our args
 153     if implicit_pip:
 154         args += ["pip"]
 155     if implicit_setuptools:
 156         args += ["setuptools"]
 157     if implicit_wheel:
 158         args += ["wheel"]
 159     # Pipenv modifications here.
 160     args += ["pipenv"]
 161     delete_tmpdir = False
 162     try:
 163         # Create a temporary directory to act as a working directory if we were
 164         # not given one.
 165         if tmpdir is None:
 166             tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp()
 167             delete_tmpdir = True
 168         # We need to extract the SSL certificates from requests so that they
 169         # can be passed to --cert
 170         cert_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, "cacert.pem")
 171         with open(cert_path, "wb") as cert:
 172             cert.write(pkgutil.get_data("pip._vendor.requests", "cacert.pem"))
 173         # Execute the included pip and use it to install the latest pip and
 174         # setuptools from PyPI
 175         sys.exit(pip.main(["install", "--upgrade"] + args))
 176     finally:
 177         # Remove our temporary directory
 178         if delete_tmpdir and tmpdir:
 179             shutil.rmtree(tmpdir, ignore_errors=True)
 180 
 181 
 182 def main():
 183     tmpdir = None
 184     try:
 185         # Create a temporary working directory
 186         tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp()
 187         # Unpack the zipfile into the temporary directory
 188         pip_zip = os.path.join(tmpdir, "pip.zip")
 189         with open(pip_zip, "wb") as fp:
 190             fp.write(b85decode(DATA.replace(b"\n", b"")))
 191         # Add the zipfile to sys.path so that we can import it
 192         sys.path.insert(0, pip_zip)
 193         # Run the bootstrap
 194         bootstrap(tmpdir=tmpdir)
 195     finally:
 196         # Clean up our temporary working directory
 197         if tmpdir:
 198             shutil.rmtree(tmpdir, ignore_errors=True)
